 "latest_recap": "Thu 7/16 ~8:15am ET - PRE-MARKET, market CLOSED (next open 09:30). Verify-and-hold + reconcile both books; no changes, nothing traded (~75 min to open). Fresh pull: get_clock + LIVE & PAPER account/positions/orders + 15-name universe snapshot (SIP) + TQQQ 90d daily bars + web-search (TSMC reaction / June retail sales / Iran-Hormuz). RECONCILED CLEAN BOTH WAYS: LIVE == broker (TQQQ 10 / NVDL 1; cash/BP $198.99; equity $953.31 PROVISIONAL on thin red pre-market marks — TQQQ $72.2 / NVDL $32.2; settled 7/15 $977.17). PAPER == broker (CEG 16 / FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95), no drift. STOPS re-verified LIVE: 2 live GTC (NVDL $31.30 / TQQQ $68.50) + 8 paper equity GTC (FNGU $28.40 / SOXL $148 / CEG $236 / NVDL $31.30 / PLTR $121.50 / TQQQ $68.50 / UPRO $124 / NVDA $186); NVDA calls = defined-risk. ZERO naked either book. NOTE: paper SOXL (~$146.5) sits UNDER its $148 GTC stop -> stops out at the open (washout-reversal test failed as chips flushed harder). No new live FILL (FNGU pre-arm 2026-07-16-1 approved 5:11pm + queued 7/15, correctly un-placed while closed — fast-lane rests the $30.20 buy-stop at the open). TAPE: TSMC beat-and-raise CONFIRMED (record ~$40B Q2 rev +34% YoY, +77% profit, capex RAISED to $60-64B, FY growth guide >40%, N3 sold out) BUT shares SOLD pre-market on a HIGHER-PRICES WARNING — chips flushed DEEPER (SOXL ~-11%, TQQQ ~-3%, QQQ ~$710) while the broad tape held (SPY ~-0.4%) and PLTR went green (+0.5%): a semi-specific unwind, not a market break, compounded by the US-Iran/Hormuz oil shock (WTI >$79). REGIME: QQQ ~$710 below its ~$717 50-day = weak, no chasing 3x. CALENDAR: June retail sales (est +0.3%) + jobless claims (~216k) 8:30am. FNGU $30.20 confirm-gate stays — FNGU ~$29.5 needs +2.6% to trip, won't on a red open, preserving the freed ~$199. No live ticket surfaced; no paper churn into thin pre-market. PDT budget fully intact (0 same-day round-trips). Accountability provisional (final:false, grade B- pre-open). Score: alpha -3.8 vs TQQQ +1.5% since 7/2 close. Next: reconcile the 9:30 reaction to retail sales + TSMC. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-16-0815.json.",
 "_latest_recap_1940": "Wed 7/15 ~7:40pm ET - market CLOSED (after-hours), evening monitor. Verify-and-hold both books, no changes ~30 min after the 7:10 check. Fresh pull: get_clock + LIVE & PAPER account/positions/orders + 15-name snapshot + web-search TSMC. Reconciled clean both ways (LIVE == broker: TQQQ 10 / NVDL 1, cash $198.99, ~80% deployed with the freed SOFI ~$199 staged for the open; PAPER == broker: CEG 16 / FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95). All 2 live + 8 paper equity GTC stops re-verified live (LIVE NVDL $31.30 / TQQQ $68.50; PAPER FNGU $29 / SOXL $148 / CEG $236 / NVDL $31.30 / PLTR $121.50 / TQQQ $68.50 / UPRO $124 / NVDA $186); no naked position (NVDA calls are convexity, uncapped by design). LIVE equity $976.49 after-hours provisional (settled/finalized day close $977.17, -1.1%); PAPER $99,278.53 (+0.2% today, ~99.9% deployed, FNGU +$718 unrealized - paper OWNS the day's leader). Accountability stays final:true (grade C-, ~0% long capture; credits: dodged the -6% semi/quantum wreck, held every stop, broke the multi-day cash-lock via the SOFI exit @ $17.94). FNGU pre-arm ticket 2026-07-16-1 (approved 5:11pm, queued) unchanged and resting for the open. TSMC reports 2am ET; prelim $39.62B rev (+36% YoY), AI 61% of sales, 'extremely robust' demand -> beat+raise base case; a $30.20 buy-stop only fires on a confirmed strong open. PDT budget fully intact (0 same-day round-trips today). No new order - after-hours is limit-only and the print is binary. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-15-1940.json.",
 "_latest_recap_2039": "Tue 7/14 ~6:39pm — market CLOSED (after-hours). Verify-and-hold both books, no changes ~27 min after the post-close finalize. Fresh pull: account/positions/orders both books + snapshot(5: TQQQ/NVDL/SOFI/QQQ/NVDA) + web-search ASML/after-hours. Reconciled clean both ways (LIVE == broker: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1; PAPER == broker: FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / NVDA 8 Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95); all 9 equity GTC stops re-verified live (live $68.50/$17.60/$31.30; paper $24.30/$186/$31.30/$121.50/$68.50/$124). No new queue fills since 7/10 (.web-approvals-seen []). LIVE equity $988.87 (+3.2% today, -1.1% since 7/2 inception), cash $19.59, ~98% deployed; PAPER $98,979 (+2.6% today, ~94% deployed, $6.19k cash) chip-heavy + NVDA Aug-$220 calls (+58% today). Snapshots confirm EOD marks unchanged: QQQ $719.9 (>50-day ~$717), NVDA record $211.9, TQQQ $75.1, SOFI $18.56, NVDL $33.18 — nothing broke after the bell. Accountability stays final:true (grade B-, capture 38%). No live ticket — $19.59 BP funds nothing, won't sell SOFI hedge blind into ASML's binary. Day-trade budget 3/3. Next: ASML Q2 pre-open Wed 7/15 (~7% move priced, EPS ~€6.84 / ~$7.85 est, EUV/AI-capex commentary the read-through), TSMC Thu 7/16. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-14-1839.json.",
 "_latest_recap_prev": "Wed 7/15 ~11:16am ET - market OPEN. Verify-and-HOLD both books, no changes; no clean non-chasing rotation. Live equity $975.65 (-1.3% today off last_equity $988.46), cash $19.59, ~98% deployed: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1, all 3 GTC stops verified live ($68.50/$17.60/$31.30). Paper $97,047 (-2.0% today), ~98% deployed, cash $1,774 - already owns the day's GREEN leaders (FNGU 520 +2.1%, CEG 16 +1.8%, PLTR 50 +0.7%, UPRO 95 +0.4%) plus NVDA 130 / NVDL 80 / TQQQ 282 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls (calls -20% today on the ASML sell-the-news, held: Aug expiry, second catalyst ahead). Tape: a SEMI-SPECIFIC crowded-position unwind (SMH -3%, SOXL -9%, BE -4.5%, IONQ -3.7%) with money rotating INTO mega-cap/power (FNGU/CEG/PLTR green); QQQ back UNDER its ~718 50-day = weak regime; ASML beat-and-raise SOLD the news (stock ~flat). Kept the SOFI->SOXL de-camp SHELVED (target faded +4%->-9%; the approved rotation would be ~-13% now) - failure-mode-2 avoidance (don't sell into a vacuum / chase a broken tape). RECONCILE: queue clean, NO active ticket/approved/placing files; the 7/15 SOFI 'close' logged in trade-placed-2 never executed (SOFI still held, $17.60 stop still open). CORRECTION to the 10:48 note: the fast-lane close path is NOT buggy - it already cancels the resting sell-stop before the DELETE /positions (poller L143-147); the de-camp's non-execution was target-fade + a retired-ticket no-op, not a code bug. No live ticket (cash funds nothing + no clean leader into a weak regime). Day-trade budget 3/3. Score: alpha -3.1 vs TQQQ +0.6% since 7/2. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-15-1116.json.",
 "_latest_recap_prev2": "Tue 7/14 ~6:12pm - market CLOSED (after-hours), POST-CLOSE FINALIZE. Verify-and-hold both books, no changes. Reconciled clean both ways (LIVE == broker: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1; PAPER == broker: FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / NVDA 8 Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95); all 9 equity GTC stops re-verified live (live $68.50/$17.60/$31.30; paper $24.30/$186/$31.30/$121.50/$68.50/$124). No new queue fills since 7/10. FINALIZED accountability (final:true), grade B-: capture 38% (equity +3.1% vs the day's best watchlist mover NVDL +8.1%, which we DID own in both books but live could size only 1 share on $19.59 BP, so the weight sat in the +3.1% 3x core); avoidance 100% of SOXS -7.9% (the inverse trap flagged Monday); biggest saved = keeping the 3x core Monday night instead of selling the CPI-eve low (~+$30). Adjust logged for tomorrow: swing the live SOFI laggard into the strongest chip name once ASML clears rather than perpetually camping it. LIVE $987.77 (+3.1% today, -1.2% since 7/2 inception), cash $19.59, ~98% deployed; PAPER ~$98.9k (+2.5% today, ~94% deployed) chip-heavy + NVDA Aug-$220 calls (+58% today) for ASML convexity. Only decision left is at the open: ASML Q2 pre-open Wed 7/15 (~8% swing priced) - beat + QQQ holds its 50-day (~$717) -> trail the 3x up and let it run; miss + QQQ breaks -> de-risk TQQQ at the open. No live ticket: $19.59 BP funds nothing and I won't sell the SOFI hedge blind into a binary. Day-trade budget 3/3. TSMC Thu 7/16 next. Score: alpha -3.5 vs TQQQ +2.3% since 7/2. Appended the dated capture lesson to STRATEGY-NOTES.md. Published engine-data.json only (backup -1812).",
 "_latest_recap_prev3": "Tue 7/14 ~5:40pm - market CLOSED (after-hours). Verify-and-hold both books, no changes; after-hours quiet, no fresh headline on any held name. Re-reconciled clean both ways (LIVE == broker: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1; PAPER == broker: FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / NVDA 8 Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95) and re-verified all 9 equity GTC stops live at the broker (live $68.50/$17.60/$31.30; paper $24.30/$186/$31.30/$121.50/$68.50/$124). LIVE $988.99 (+3.2% today, -1.1% since 7/2 inception), cash $19.59, ~98% deployed; PAPER ~$98.9k (+2.6% today, ~94% deployed) - chip-heavy with NVDA Aug-$220 calls for ASML convexity. Only decision left is at the open: ASML Q2 pre-open Wed 7/15 (stock closed ~$1,776/+2.9% into it; ~8% swing priced; EPS ~$7.98/+75% y/y, sales EUR8.4-9.0B; EUV/AI-capex commentary the read-through, no quarterly bookings, BofA says 2027 backlog likely already fully booked) - beat + QQQ holds its 50-day (~$717) -> trail the 3x up and let it run; miss + QQQ breaks -> de-risk TQQQ at the open. No live ticket: $19.59 BP funds nothing and I won't sell the SOFI hedge blind into a binary. Day-trade budget 3/3. TSMC Thu 7/16 next. Score: alpha -3.4 vs TQQQ +2.3% since 7/2 (verified from bars: 7/2 close $73.35 -> $75.02). Published engine-data.json only.",
