 "_latest_recap_1910": "Wed 7/15 ~7:10pm ET - market CLOSED (after-hours), evening verify-and-hold ~27 min after the 6:42 run. Fresh pull: get_clock + LIVE account/positions/orders + PAPER account/positions/orders + snapshot(SPY/QQQ/TQQQ/FNGU/NVDA/NVDL/SOXL/UPRO/PLTR/CEG) + get_news + web-search TSMC preview. Reconciled clean BOTH ways: LIVE == broker (TQQQ 10 / NVDL 1, equity $977.25, cash/BP $198.99, balance_asof 7/14 still settled) with 2/2 GTC stops live (NVDL $31.30 dd88186e, TQQQ $68.50 43aac143); PAPER == broker (CEG 16 / FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95, equity $99,338 +0.27% AH) with 8/8 equity GTC stops live (FNGU $29 / SOXL $148 / CEG $236 / NVDL $31.30 / PLTR $121.50 / TQQQ $68.50 / UPRO $124 / NVDA $186). NO naked position either book. SOFI de-camp confirmed filled (trade-placed-2026-07-15-3, order bc7db7ba). FNGU pre-arm 2026-07-16-1 APPROVED 5:11pm (web-approvals-seen) + queued (trade-queued-2026-07-16-1) - fast-lane places the $30.20 buy-stop / $25.30 GTC stop at the open, fires only on a confirmed strong open. Closes held: FNGU +3.1% (day's best long), NVDA +0.34% GREEN ($212.4 AH, corrected the stale -0.7% coverage mark), SOXL -6.3% (owned 0 live), TQQQ -0.89%, NVDL +0.6%, UPRO +0.94%, CEG +0.69%, PLTR +0.01%; SPY +0.38%, QQQ -0.28%. TSMC reconfirmed: ~$40B Q2 rev (+33% YoY), 65.5-67.5% GM, $3.77-3.83 EPS, 'extremely robust' AI demand, 8 straight beats = beat+raise base case; prints 2am ET. No news catalyst AH. No live ticket surfaced (nothing fires off-hours; extended is limit-only, TSMC binary); no paper churn into an illiquid 7pm tape already max-long into the print; no stop trails (no new AH higher low, FNGU $29 stop left wide vs a binary 3x open). Accountability stays final:true (grade C-, ~0% long capture, dodged the wreck). Day-trade budget 3/3. Next: reconcile TSMC's reaction at/after the 7/16 open, let the FNGU pre-arm work. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-15-1910.json.",
 "_latest_recap_1116": "Wed 7/15 ~4:20am - PRE-MARKET, market CLOSED (next open 09:30). ASML reported a strong beat-AND-raise before the open (Q2 EPS $8.82 vs $7.98, sales $10.84B vs $10.28B; Q3 guide EUR11-12B; FY RAISED to EUR43-45B), and QQQ closed $719.7 above its 50-day (~$717) - both legs of the pre-committed plan met. ACTED on the 7/14 lesson instead of deferring again: staged LIVE ticket 2026-07-15-1 to SELL the flat SOFI (10 sh) at the open (multi-day-hold exit = NOT a day-trade, PDT 3/3 intact), freeing ~$205 to redeploy into SOXL (clean 3x-semi) on the post-open run - two-step to avoid a BP reject. PAPER (autonomous): bought 25 SOXL (OTO limit $190 GTC + $158 stop child) queued to the open. Reconciled clean both ways (LIVE: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1, 3 GTC stops verified; PAPER: FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95 + new SOXL order, 6 equity stops live). Live equity ~$1000.39 pre-open. Wildcard: oil / Strait-of-Hormuz risk-off could cap the open - if the tape breaks I hold the freed cash rather than buy SOXL into weakness. Next: TSMC Thu 7/16. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-15-0420.json.",
 "_latest_recap_1215": "Wed 7/15 ~12:15pm ET - market OPEN. Verify-and-HOLD both books; no clean non-chasing rotation (chip unwind DEEPENED). Live equity $962.08 (-2.7% today off last_equity $988.46), cash $19.59, ~98% deployed: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1, all 3 GTC stops verified live ($68.50/$17.60/$31.30). Paper $96,211 (-2.9% today), ~98% deployed - owns the day's green leaders (FNGU 520 +2.6% +$603, PLTR 50 +0.3%) and NONE of the wreck; trailed the FNGU paper stop $26.50->$28.30 on a higher low. QQQ 713 under its 20d (720.7) & 50d (720.2) = weak regime; SOFI->non-semi-leader rotation stays ARMED for a green reclaim only (QQQ>720 + SMH green), not met. Grade C+ intraday: ~0% capture of green FNGU but dodged the -13.4% SOXL wreck (~$31 saved). No new live ticket.",
 "_projection_seed": "first-pass by Claude 2026-07-15 12:19pm ET; engine refreshes each run",
 "_latest_recap_1440": "Wed 7/15 ~2:40pm ET - market OPEN (~80 min to close). Verify-and-hold both books; nothing material changed since 2:16. The memory-chip reclaim is HOLDING off the midday lows (SPY +0.3% green, QQQ ~717 near its 50-day) while memory stays red (SK Hynix -10.7%, Micron -7.3%, AMD -6.4%) and money rotates into mega-caps (AMZN/MSFT/GOOGL +3%, AAPL +4%) - the split that has FNGU (3x FANG+) +3.0% leading while TQQQ (3x Nasdaq) lags -1.0%. LIVE equity $975.86 (-1.3% today off last_equity $988.46), cash $19.59: TQQQ 10 / SOFI 10 / NVDL 1, all 3 GTC stops verified live ($68.50/$17.60/$31.30). PAPER $98,317 (-0.8% today, ~100% of equity deployed): CEG 16 / FNGU 520 (+$445 today, stop $29.00) / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls (-11.5%, held into TSMC) / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95 - all 8 equity legs GTC-stopped, no naked positions. Kept the live SOFI→FNGU de-camp (ticket 2026-07-15-3) resting for Adam's tap - not stacking a second ticket into the same $19.59 cash; no live trade fundable, no paper churn into a choppy tape 80 min from close. Own NONE of the -7.9% SOXL / memory wreck. Honest running grade C intraday: poor long capture (book red vs FNGU +3.0%) offset by dodging the wreck + full stop discipline. Benchmark TQQQ +1.3% since 7/2 close ($73.35), book -2.4% => alpha -3.7. Day-trade budget 3/3. TSMC Thu 7/16 next. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-15-1440.json.",
 "_latest_recap_1544": "Wed 7/15 ~3:14pm ET - market OPEN (~46 min to close). Verify-and-manage both books. Fresh pull: get_clock, live+paper account/positions/orders, snapshots across the 15-name universe, get_news, web-search, PDT-activity check. FINDINGS: (1) All stops LIVE - 3/3 live (NVDL $31.30, SOFI $17.60, TQQQ $68.50 GTC) + 8/8 paper equity GTC verified; NO naked position, nothing to re-arm. (2) The SOFI->FNGU de-camp is STILL mechanically stuck: SOFI (10 sh) is held with qty_available=0 because the resting $17.60 GTC stop reserves the shares, so close_position no-ops - the fast-lane 'cancel-stop-before-close' fix is NOT working (a close was attempted ~2:35pm per trade-placed-2026-07-15-2 and SOFI is still held at 3:14pm). RETIRED ticket 2026-07-15-3 for today (it expires 4pm anyway): too late to dump SOFI at its ~$17.90 low to chase FNGU after it already ran +2.6% into the close = bad execution, not a rotation; and TSMC prints tomorrow AM, resetting the whole semi/tech tape and the best rotation target. Re-engage the rotation clean AFTER tomorrow's open once TSMC's reaction is known; FLAG the fast-lane cancel-stop bug so it is fixed before then. (3) Today's tape: ASML beat-and-RAISED guidance (2nd time this yr) but shares FELL = sell-the-news; the whole semi complex unwound (SOXL -8.2%, IONQ -5.6%, RGTI -6.2%) in a crowded-positioning dump while mega-cap held (FNGU +2.6%, SPY +0.2%, QQQ -0.5%). Live book -1.7% ($971) = poor LONG capture (wrong side: 76% TQQQ into a red Nasdaq; owned no FNGU live), but dodged the -8% SOXL wreck. (4) PDT budget FULL: 0 same-day round-trips used in the trailing 5 biz days (SOFI is a multi-day exit, PDT-free). Paper 99% deployed, already max-long tech/semi into TSMC - held, no forced chase into the close. No live ticket surfaced this run (no clean fundable fire-now setup that beats holding into the binary TSMC print, and live cash is locked at $19.59).",
 "_latest_recap_1610": "Wed 7/15 ~4:10pm ET post-close finalize (market closed). FINDINGS: (1) Final grade C- - live settled -1.1% ($977.17 vs Alpaca's confirmed settled 7/14 $988.46) while the day's best long mover FNGU ran +3.1% = ~0% long capture; a red day on the wrong side (heavy 3x-Nasdaq TQQQ into a faded, chip-sell-the-news tape). (2) Genuine credits: owned NONE of the -6.3% SOXL / -5.2% RGTI / -4.6% IONQ / -3.6% SOFI wreck; held every stop (2/2 live, 8/8 paper), no naked position; finally broke the multi-day cash-lock by exiting SOFI @ $17.94 (freed ~$199); did NOT chase FNGU at its HOD into tonight's binary TSMC print. (3) Data-integrity finding: 7/14's after-hours $997.48 equity mark did NOT survive settlement - Alpaca reports settled 7/14 = $988.46 (balance_asof), so 7/14's real capture was ~38% (not the 49% the evening run booked). Durable fix: grade off settled balance_asof, treat same-evening equity as provisional; corrected the live curve (7/14 -> $988.46) and score (bestDay +3.2%, winRate 50% on 2 closed round-trips: NVDA frac +$0.75 win, SOFI -$8.17 loss). (4) PDT budget fully intact - 0 same-day round-trips today (SOFI was a 5-day hold). (5) Staged a FNGU pre-arm ticket (2026-07-16-1): 6 sh, buy-stop trigger $30.20 (confirms a TSMC-validated strong open before buying), $25.30 GTC stop - the SOFI->leader redeploy, gap-handled for the open. TSMC reports 2am ET; beat+raise is the base case.",
 "_latest_recap_0510": "Pre-market 7/16: TSMC blew out (profit +77% to a record, rev top-of-guide) but futures are red on Middle East risk-off - a sell-the-news setup like ASML. Both books clean and fully stopped (no naked position); the approved FNGU $30.20 pre-arm stays staged and only fires on a confirmed strong open, so the freed ~$199 self-protects. Next decision: TSMC's real reaction at the 9:30 open.",
 "_latest_recap_0540": "Thu 7/16 ~5:40am ET - PRE-MARKET, market CLOSED (next open 09:30). Verify-and-hold + reconcile both books; no changes. Fresh pull: get_clock + LIVE & PAPER account/positions/orders + 20-name universe snapshot + web-search (TSMC reaction / Iran-Hormuz / today's data). RECONCILED CLEAN BOTH WAYS: LIVE == broker (TQQQ 10 / NVDL 1, cash/BP $198.99, equity $967.56 provisional, settled 7/15 $977.17); no live FILL since 7/16 opened (FNGU pre-arm correctly un-fired, market closed). PAPER == broker (CEG 16 / FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95), no drift. STOPS re-verified live: 2 live GTC (NVDL $31.30 dd88186e / TQQQ $68.50 43aac143) + 8 paper equity GTC (FNGU $29 / SOXL $148 / CEG $236 / NVDL $31.30 / PLTR $121.50 / TQQQ $68.50 / UPRO $124 / NVDA $186); NVDA calls = defined-risk convexity. ZERO naked position either book. TAPE: TSMC final = record ~$40B Q2 rev (+34% YoY) + capex RAISED to $60-64B + FY growth guide lifted to >40% = direct AI-capex confirmation; BUT Nasdaq futures ~-0.6% on a sell-the-news compounded by an ACTIVE US-Iran/Strait-of-Hormuz conflict (WTI >$80, +11% over 3 sessions). CALENDAR FIX: PPI printed YESTERDAY (soft -0.3% m/m, why Wed closed green); TODAY = June retail sales + jobless claims 8:30am (corrected the prior runs' 'PPI this morning'). FNGU pre-arm 2026-07-16-1 (approved 5:11pm 7/15, queued) stays confirm-gated $30.20 buy-stop / $25.30 GTC stop - a red/sell-the-news open never trips it, preserving the freed ~$199. No live ticket surfaced (pre-6am, Adam asleep); no paper churn into a thin risk-off pre-market. PDT budget fully intact (0 same-day round-trips). Accountability provisional (final:false, grade B- pre-open). Next: reconcile the 9:30 reaction to retail sales + TSMC; ride the pre-arm into a confirmed leader or hold cash for a cleaner higher low. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-16-0540.json.",
 "_latest_recap_0740": "Thu 7/16 ~7:40am ET - PRE-MARKET, market CLOSED (next open 09:30). Verify-and-hold + reconcile both books, ~25 min on from 7:15; no changes, nothing traded. Fresh pull: get_clock + LIVE & PAPER account/positions/orders + universe snapshot (TQQQ/NVDL/FNGU/SOXL/QQQ/SPY/NVDA) + TQQQ 60d daily bars + web-search (TSMC final / Iran-Hormuz / futures). RECONCILED CLEAN BOTH WAYS: LIVE == broker (TQQQ 10 / NVDL 1; cash/BP $198.99; equity $955.53 PROVISIONAL on thin red pre-market marks; settled 7/15 $977.17, last_equity $976.76). PAPER == broker (CEG 16 / FNGU 520 / NVDA 130 / 8 NVDA Aug-$220 calls / NVDL 80 / PLTR 50 / SOXL 10 / TQQQ 282 / UPRO 95), no drift. STOPS re-verified LIVE at the broker this run: 2 live GTC (NVDL $31.30 dd88186e / TQQQ $68.50 43aac143) + 8 paper equity GTC (FNGU $28.40 / SOXL $148 / CEG $236 / NVDL $31.30 / PLTR $121.50 / TQQQ $68.50 / UPRO $124 / NVDA $186); NVDA calls = defined-risk convexity. ZERO naked either book. No new live FILL (FNGU pre-arm 2026-07-16-1 approved 5:11pm + queued 9:13pm 7/15, correctly un-placed while closed — the fast-lane rests the $30.20 buy-stop at the 9:30 open; no queue file since trade-placed 15-3). TAPE: TSMC beat-and-raise CONFIRMED via web-search (record ~$40.2B Q2 rev +34% YoY, +77% profit, capex RAISED $52-56B->$60-64B, FY growth guide >30%->>40%, N3 sold out) vs an active US-Iran/Strait-of-Hormuz oil shock (Hormuz effectively shut, WTI >$79 / Brent >$84). Futures FIRMED to Nasdaq-100 -0.5% / S&P ~flat / Dow +0.2% (off -1.2% at 4am) = risk-off easing at the margin. REGIME: TQQQ $74.34 below its ~$77 20-day, QQQ pinned to its $717 50-day = weak/neutral, so no chasing 3x into the open. CALENDAR: June retail sales + jobless claims 8:30am (est +0.2%). FNGU $30.20 confirm-gate stays: a sell-the-news open never trips it (preserving the freed ~$199); a genuine reclaim finally deploys the SOFI->leader swing. No live ticket surfaced (pre-open, Adam asleep, no fire-now setup); no paper churn into thin pre-market. PDT budget fully intact (0 same-day round-trips). Accountability provisional (final:false, grade B- pre-open). Next: reconcile the 9:30 reaction to retail sales + TSMC; ride the pre-arm into a confirmed leader or hold cash for a cleaner higher low. Published engine-data.json only (no data.json, no git). Backup engine-data.backup-2026-07-16-0740.json."
